init_text: Humans once wielded formidable magical power. But with over 7 billion of us on the planet now, Mana has spread far too thinly to have any effect. When hostile aliens reduce humanity to a mere fraction, the survivors discover an old power has begun to reawaken once again.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Dwarves have mined the earth for centuries, creating huge underground cities and a lush eco-system beneath the surface.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: But when they finally come into contact with humans, their fabled underground wealth proves to be the least of humanityâ€™s worries.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: On the surface, humans and elves live in peaceful coexistence.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Elves are slowly becoming a less powerful race and are losing land in the process.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The elves are secretly killing off humans.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The elves are poisoning the water and food supply.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They decided that the elves needed to be dealt with.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The elves had a large advantage in numbers, but that didn't matter.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The elves were losing their power and the humans were gaining it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The elves were satisfied with the deal, but the humans soon made an amendment to it.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: They wanted all the remaining elves to move to a reservation.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: The elves reluctantly agreed and moved to the reservation.
